hopobject.body: Do you know what extension he's on? healthandblissforlife.com The group transformed from a once marginal organization with a few thousand supporters to a party represented in parliament with popularity ratings reaching as high as 12 percent in June. Yet it took the Sept. 18 killing of Fyssas to trigger a high-level investigation into its activities that culminated in a rapid series of arrests over the weekend of 20 Golden Dawn members including its leader and five other lawmakers.
